Material UI

1. npm install --save @angular/material @angular/cdk @angular/animations

2. Once the animations package is installed, import BrowserAnimationsModule into your application to enable animations support.

import {BrowserAnimationsModule} from '@angular/platform-browser/animations';

@NgModule({
  ...
  imports: [BrowserAnimationsModule],
  ...
})


3. import the component module you want to use

import {MatToolbarModule} from '@angular/material/toolbar';

 then add "MatToolbarModule"  to imports section

4. include a theme

goto styles.css and then add the below

5. Gesture Support

npm install --save hammerjs
